{"lemma":"شارِدٌ","slug":"شارِدٌ","root":"ش.ر.د","root_slug":"ش-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22095"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fugitive; runaway; deserter; defector","examples":[{"text":"رَجُلٌ شَارِدٌ","english":"a fugitive man"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"straying; astray","examples":[{"text":"حَيَوَانٌ شَارِدٌ","english":"a stray animal"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"frightened; intimidated; helpless; at a loss","examples":[{"text":"كَانَ شَارِدًا","english":"he was frightened / at a loss"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"absent-minded; distracted","examples":[{"text":"شَارِدُ الْفِكْرِ","english":"absent-minded"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"uprooted; lacking stability; vagrant","examples":[{"text":"إِنْسَانٌ شَارِدٌ","english":"a rootless person"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vagrant; tramp; vagabond","examples":[{"text":"يَعِيشُ كَشَارِدٍ","english":"he lives as a vagabond"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"irregularity; anomaly (especially in language)","examples":[{"text":"شَوَارِدُ اللُّغَةِ","english":"irregularities of the language"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From شَرَدَ (šarada, “to flee, run away, stray”), from the root ش ر د (š r d)."},"ipa":["/ʃaː.rid/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22095","headword_ar":"شَارِدٌ","root":"$rd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aruwdN","text_ar":"شَرُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, L, K,) applied to a camel, (S, A, L,) and to a horse or the like, (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Taking fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shying, and fleeing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running away at random;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refractory, and going away at random,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breaking loose, and going hither and thither by reason of sprightliness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that takes fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (S, L, K:) [or] the latter [signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wont to take fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and] is applied to a male animal and to a female: (L:) [the fem. of the former is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":":] pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~adN","text_ar":"شُرَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * L) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aradN","text_ar":"شَرَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) [or rather this is a quasi-pl. n.,] like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadamN","text_ar":"خَدَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAdimN","text_ar":"خَادِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) [and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAridapN","text_ar":"شَارِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~adN","text_ar":"شُرَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awaAridu","text_ar":"شَوَارِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aruwdN","text_ar":"شَرُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urudN","text_ar":"شُرُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuburN","text_ar":"زُبُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zabuwrN","text_ar":"زَبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, L, K. *) You say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN $aruwdN","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ شَرُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mare, refractory towards the rider:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN $aruwdN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ شَرُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel that runs away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breaks loose and goes hither and thither by reason of her sprightliness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAfiyapN $aruwdN","text_ar":"قَافِيَةٌ شَرُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rhyme,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poem, current through the countries, lands,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"through the cities,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towns."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawaAfK $awaAridu","text_ar":"قَوَافٍ شَوَارِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abd","text_ar":"ابد"},{"kind":"text","text":") and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawaAfK $ur~ado","text_ar":"قَوَافٍ شُرَّدْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K ibid.) [pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAfiyapN","text_ar":"قَافِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAridapN","text_ar":"شَارِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strange, unusual, unfamiliar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extraordinary, rhymes"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verses"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"i